Reasoning: The paper discusses the performance of maximum-likelihood decoding on the binary erasure channel for low-density parity-check codes, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new low-complexity near-ML decoding algorithm for quasi-cyclic LDPC codes, which could fall under the computer communication (cs.CC) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses distance properties of random codes, which could fall under the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents upper bounds on the ML decoding error probability and performance, which could fall under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
